						               													<description>Link-Up is a tile placement game for 2-6 players ages 6 to adult that takes 60 to 90 minutes to play.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Every Link-Up tile has up to four open chain links. Each of these links may be one of the four link colors: red, blue, green, or yellow. A player has a pool of up to five tiles that they keep hidden from other players behind a screen. On their turn, a player plays any number of tiles from their hand and scores points for each chain or loop completed by the tiles played. At the end of their turn a player draws up to two tiles to a maximum hand size of five.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The player with the most points when the tiles run out is the winner.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;See www.linkupgame.com for more details.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
